proof_block:
// The single ensures `cloned_ep@ == ep@` gives, for each run,
// `r1@ == ep@` and `r2@ == ep@`. Transitivity of `==` on the
// `AbstractEndPoint` struct (and on the underlying `Seq<u8>`)
// yields `r1@ == r2@`, but z3 only sees this once we lift the
// chain (and the seq-extensionality witness) into the proof
// context as explicit implications, so the determinism
// postcondition `P ==> det_clone_end_point_equal(r1, r2)`
// becomes derivable.
assert((r1@ == ep@) && (r2@ == ep@) ==> r1@ == r2@);
assert((r1@ == ep@) && (r2@ == ep@) ==> r1.id@ == r2.id@);
assert((r1@ == ep@) && (r2@ == ep@) ==> r1.id@ =~= r2.id@);
assert((r1@ == ep@) && (r2@ == ep@) ==> r1.id@.len() == r2.id@.len());
